/**
 * Trying to bypass by only using one port class.
 * This fails beacuse the operators are left associative: The operation A:B
 * is performed first and port A.y is assigned to class up (because it is
 * the left operator). A connection with C.y is then impossible (because C.y
 * also has class up)
 */

A = box fa( out x, out y )
B = box fb( in x, out z )
C = box fc( in z, up in y )

connect A:B:C
